BENGAL

3
00:00:22,900 --> 00:00:26,136
KANO RYU
KOMIYA TAKAYASU

4
00:00:26,136 --> 00:00:36,170
Kimi ga haita shiroi iki ga ima yukkuri kaze ni notte
<i>Misty white breaths you exhale, now gently riding on the wind</i>

5
00:00:36,170 --> 00:00:38,880
Sora ni ukabu kumo no naka ni sukoshi zutsu kiete yuku
<i>Into the clouds in the sky, gradually fading away</i>

6
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:43,120
SAKUMA YUI / OKAYAMA YUTA / MOTOYAMA AYUMI
Sora ni ukabu kumo no naka ni sukoshi zutsu kiete yuku
<i>Into the clouds in the sky, gradually fading away</i>

7
00:00:43,120 --> 00:00:46,143
Sora ni ukabu kumo no naka ni sukoshi zutsu kiete yuku
<i>Into the clouds in the sky, gradually fading away</i>

8
00:00:46,494 --> 00:00:50,930
NAKAYAMA YUICHIRO / UNO SHOHEI
KOBAYASHI ASAKO / HIRATA KAORU
Toku takai sora no naka de te o nobasu shiroi kumo
<i>From up above in the sky white clouds reach down</i>

9
00:00:50,930 --> 00:00:55,481
Toku takai sora no naka de te o nobasu shiroi kumo
<i>From up above in the sky white clouds reach down</i>

10
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,387
NAGASHIMA EIKO
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

11
00:00:57,387 --> 00:01:01,879
<i>At the end of the day, when people are rushing home...</i>
NAGASHIMA EIKO
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

12
00:01:01,879 --> 00:01:04,210
<i>...That's when my day starts.</i>
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

13
00:01:04,210 --> 00:01:07,451
Director: MATSUOKA JOJI
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

14
00:01:07,451 --> 00:01:15,860
Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne
<i>Always seems like a thing of the past</i>

15
00:01:17,482 --> 00:01:21,935
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

16
00:01:21,935 --> 00:01:27,007
<i>My business hours start from midnight to 7 am.</i>
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

17
00:01:27,270 --> 00:01:31,800
<i>People call my restaurant 'the late night diner.'</i>

18
00:01:32,940 --> 00:01:34,910
[MESHIYA]

19
00:01:35,406 --> 00:01:40,271
<i>Do customers come? You ask...
There's quite a number who do.</i>

20
00:01:42,239 --> 00:01:50,620
<i>Wabi-Sabi Subs presents:</i>
<b>SHINYA SHOKUDO Season 3</b>
EP 7: "Freshwater Clam Soup..."

21
00:01:53,508 --> 00:01:55,300
Say, that boardwalk over there...

22
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:58,360
<i>Every Saturday morning, Mr. and Mrs. Hiraga...</i>

23
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:02,220
<i>...would go out walking and stop here
to eat breakfast along the way...</i>

24
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:04,300
<i>...for a month now.</i>

25
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:05,660
Good Morning, Master.

26
00:02:05,660 --> 00:02:07,040
Good morning.

27
00:02:11,620 --> 00:02:15,530
Since I started eating breakfast here,
I feel my body has changed for the better.

28
00:02:15,836 --> 00:02:19,050
The breakfast here is nothing special.

29
00:02:19,540 --> 00:02:21,280
It must be your morning walks, isn't it?

30
00:02:25,540 --> 00:02:27,820
Perhaps, it's because of the clam soup.

31
00:02:27,940 --> 00:02:31,780
Everyone says that freshwater clam soup is
a good midsummer dish for the body.

32
00:02:31,780 --> 00:02:32,830
Right?

33
00:02:34,710 --> 00:02:35,740
Master...

34
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:40,740
Please, say that I've been
here the whole time.

35
00:02:40,740 --> 00:02:42,060
What's the matter, Mine-kun?

36
00:02:42,060 --> 00:02:44,660
Well, I attended a mixer...

37
00:02:44,660 --> 00:02:50,260
How to say this... there was a girl there,
we hit it off well...

38
00:02:50,260 --> 00:02:53,080
- I unintentionally went with her to a hotel...
- "Unintentionally" huh...

39
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:56,620
I was drunk, and had accidentally fallen asleep...

40
00:02:56,620 --> 00:02:58,120
"Accidentally", huh...

41
00:02:58,740 --> 00:03:03,860
When I woke up, I had 32 missed calls
and 20 messages from my  girlfriend...

42
00:03:03,860 --> 00:03:06,860
You mean the girl you've been
going out with lately?

43
00:03:07,540 --> 00:03:10,140
Then, I'll tell her you unintentionally
spent here the whole night.

44
00:03:10,140 --> 00:03:15,810
Do you have to put it like that... Anyway she's coming
here now so please just say that I was here.

45
00:03:21,540 --> 00:03:26,150
See? I told you I'm here, right?

46
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:30,950
Hey, how about eating some breakfast? Ok?

47
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:35,630
Master!

48
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,260
I told you, it's not what you think, I swear...

49
00:03:41,260 --> 00:03:43,020
Just quit that act, and come on!

50
00:03:48,420 --> 00:03:50,770
Then, what happened to Mine-kun?

51
00:03:50,770 --> 00:03:54,510
Who knows... I haven't seen him since.

52
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:57,340
There's no way I'd forgive a guy for cheating.

53
00:03:57,340 --> 00:04:01,300
Saya-chan, if you say such a thing,
you won't be able to get married.

54
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:02,320
Why?

55
00:04:02,820 --> 00:04:05,180
There's no man who wouldn't cheat.

56
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:07,300
That's not true, I won't cheat.

57
00:04:07,300 --> 00:04:11,060
Yes you will. If you find yourself
in the right time and circumstances.

58
00:04:11,060 --> 00:04:14,020
Men always think, "If I had a chance..."

59
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:18,740
But the couple who comes here on Saturday,
I don't think they're like that.

60
00:04:18,740 --> 00:04:22,070
Right, right. The Hiraga couple.
They get along well, don't they?

61
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:26,210
You get married, occasionally have spats
and hate each other but...

62
00:04:26,340 --> 00:04:29,980
You both get to watch your children
grow up and leave home.

63
00:04:30,060 --> 00:04:33,780
Then, it'll just be the two of you,
quietly and slowly spending your days together...

64
00:04:33,780 --> 00:04:35,190
I yearn to have a life like that...

65
00:04:35,190 --> 00:04:36,180
Me too.

66
00:04:36,330 --> 00:04:39,490
You guys are really naive, huh.

67
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:46,640
Hiraga-san.

68
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:49,460
Oh... Hello.

69
00:04:49,850 --> 00:04:50,900
Welcome.

70
00:04:51,810 --> 00:04:53,880
Here you go.

71
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:57,300
Fancy seeing you here alone
in the middle of the night.

72
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:01,710
We were just talking about you,
about you being a model couple.

73
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:06,880
My wife has gone back home to Hiroshima.
It seems that a grandchild was born.

74
00:05:07,050 --> 00:05:08,500
Congratulations!

75
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:12,020
Well, it is a grandchild, but it isn't mine.

76
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:14,120
Which means...

77
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:18,580
My wife had a daughter and a son from
her two previous marriages...

78
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:21,700
It was her married daughter who gave birth.

79
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:26,370
I see... um, how did you meet your wife?

80
00:05:27,850 --> 00:05:31,110
Last summer, we had a class reunion
in our hometown.

81
00:05:31,110 --> 00:05:33,910
That's where we met again after 40 years.

82
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,398
Feels like fate, huh?

83
00:05:36,555 --> 00:05:38,675
Um, it was my first marriage.

84
00:05:40,539 --> 00:05:43,610
Last year, I too was invited to my class reunion.

85
00:05:43,610 --> 00:05:46,180
Tsk... wonder if I should have gone.

86
00:05:46,180 --> 00:05:47,820
You should have.

87
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:54,330
And then?

88
00:05:55,054 --> 00:05:58,784
"She hasn't been doing too well
after giving birth."

89
00:05:59,460 --> 00:06:01,440
Then you don't have to worry about me.

90
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:04,440
"Say, are you eating properly?"

91
00:06:05,553 --> 00:06:08,883
Yeah. Just worry over things at your end.

92
00:06:09,568 --> 00:06:10,758
"Thanks."

93
00:06:11,741 --> 00:06:12,841
Bye.

94
00:06:24,906 --> 00:06:27,316
"White, 12 of 10."

95
00:06:30,479 --> 00:06:32,019
"10 seconds."

96
00:06:34,327 --> 00:06:35,897
"20 seconds."

97
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:43,310
"1... 2... 3... 4... 5... 6..."

98
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:51,720
"20 seconds. 1... 2...3... 4..."

99
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,460
Thanks for waiting.

100
00:06:57,440 --> 00:07:00,300
Are you sure you'll only eat that?

101
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:04,700
Yeah. Actually, I just finished
eating with a co-worker...

102
00:07:05,008 --> 00:07:08,198
But for some reason,
I don't feel like going home yet.

103
00:07:08,619 --> 00:07:09,979
What would you like to drink?

104
00:07:11,758 --> 00:07:16,218
I'll pass. I become a pest
when I get drunk.

105
00:07:16,433 --> 00:07:18,553
Excuse me, another glass of beer.

106
00:07:18,638 --> 00:07:19,808
Sure thing.

107
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:27,160
Are you... um, this is just a hunch...

108
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:30,090
...um, is your work related to "Go?"

109
00:07:30,592 --> 00:07:32,712
Ah, I knew it.

110
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:38,130
Master, this person appears on TV...
Let's see... Teshigahara Mariko-san.

111
00:07:38,205 --> 00:07:39,105
Really...

112
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:43,740
You're a score keeper in the
televised game of "go", aren't you?

113
00:07:43,902 --> 00:07:46,262
This is the first time someone recognized me.

114
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:51,260
But the truth is I want to be recognized
as a professional Go player.

115
00:07:51,980 --> 00:07:57,550
I'm aiming to be a professional player,
being a scorer is just a part-time job.

116
00:07:57,837 --> 00:07:59,897
Still, you have a nice voice.

117
00:08:00,086 --> 00:08:01,906
Do you like Go?

118
00:08:02,121 --> 00:08:03,191
Not at all.

119
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:08,060
I have no idea how it goes.
I always fall asleep when watching it.

120
00:08:18,430 --> 00:08:21,960
I haven't eaten momiji manju* since elementary school.
(*maple leaf-shaped cake with sweet bean filling;
Specialty of Hiroshima)

121
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:23,380
It's my first time to eat it.

122
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:26,820
Thank you for this treat.
Considering we just met here.

123
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,480
- Are you on a business trip?
- Yes.

124
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:32,690
This guy here is the only classmate
of mine who made it to Tokyo.

125
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:36,490
You know what, Master? This guy here
is like the Cupid of Love.

126
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:37,490
Cupid?

127
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:41,310
He aggressively insisted that I attend our
junior high school reunion.

128
00:08:41,310 --> 00:08:45,240
But thanks to him, I got to meet my wife.

129
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,440
So then, Mizue-chan, right?

130
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:50,570
When we heard that she came back,
we all got together the other day.

131
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:57,510
I heard her daughter wasn't feeling so good...
so it's Mizue-chan who's taking care of the baby.

132
00:08:57,600 --> 00:09:00,600
If you have spare time, you oughta
go and see her.

133
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:05,160
I'll just be a nuisance. Besides,
it's an important time at work.

134
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,880
She'll be back next week anyway.

135
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:06,890
Oh, here, here.
She'll be back next week anyway.

136
00:09:06,890 --> 00:09:07,890
Oh, here, here.

137
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:11,930
Oh, is this Koucchan?

138
00:09:12,057 --> 00:09:16,407
Yeah, it's Kouichi. When I told him
Mizue-chan came back, he came right away.

139
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:25,310
They were once rumored to be a couple
back in high school, right?

140
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:28,680
Your wife was popular, huh.

141
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:32,480
She was garish. She wore her skirts up to here.

142
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:36,620
That's why I didn't expect that
you'd end up with her, Yoshio.

143
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,220
Ah...

144
00:09:38,970 --> 00:09:41,060
Mizue-chan went through
various relationships but...

145
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:44,840
Finally she has found her last man in you.

146
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:46,260
I'm happy for you.

147
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,920
"White, 12 of 15."

148
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:04,180
"10 seconds."

149
00:10:08,276 --> 00:10:09,636
"20 seconds."

150
00:10:11,584 --> 00:10:13,024
"25 seconds."

151
00:10:14,193 --> 00:10:16,143
"28 seconds."

152
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:21,570
"This is your 8th time for consideration.
You have 2 consideration times left."

153
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:26,600
He looks down, doesn't he?

154
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:32,040
Just heard awhile ago that
his wife hasn't yet returned.

155
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:37,050
Looks like... her son this time,
had a motorcycle accident.

156
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:43,510
Thanks for waiting.

157
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:53,400
Do not know whether it's true, that he fell down with his
motorbike and got hospitalized for a fractured clavicle.

158
00:10:55,049 --> 00:10:59,729
We got married after she came to Tokyo but...

159
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:03,500
I still wonder if she's more
comfortable over there.

160
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:06,810
...that's why, maybe she's lying to me.

161
00:11:08,029 --> 00:11:12,439
Mizue was a girl who developed earlier...

162
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:17,690
She was sexy, that's why,
I had always wanted her but...

163
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:21,870
Many things have happened in her past.

164
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:26,360
I heard she had done some things*...
(*sex industry)

165
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,400
What on earth are you saying.

166
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:33,540
"It doesn't matter whatever happened in the past..."

167
00:11:34,020 --> 00:11:36,870
That's what I thought...

168
00:11:45,578 --> 00:11:50,428
Hey... just wanna ask if your son's
collarbone has gotten better...

169
00:11:51,162 --> 00:11:52,152
You're going out?

170
00:11:52,833 --> 00:11:55,903
"I'm going to eat out with Koucchan..."

171
00:11:56,538 --> 00:11:58,888
What... The two of you?

172
00:11:59,056 --> 00:12:03,898
"I'm going to consult him regarding the accident,
like insurance procedures and the like."

173
00:12:04,187 --> 00:12:07,857
"Because Koucchan is in the car business
so he knows some details."

174
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,140
Really...

175
00:12:09,664 --> 00:12:13,024
Lucky you. You got plenty
of men to help you.

176
00:12:14,637 --> 00:12:16,027
"What's that supposed to mean?"

177
00:12:18,612 --> 00:12:20,642
"Why would you say such a thing?"

178
00:12:21,674 --> 00:12:26,994
No reason. If you like, you don't have
to come back anymore.

179
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:31,030
After all, your son, grandkid
and friends are all there...

180
00:12:31,209 --> 00:12:32,529
...including your old boyfriends...

181
00:12:33,895 --> 00:12:36,609
"The heck is that?"

182
00:12:37,267 --> 00:12:39,567
"What the blazes did you just say?"

183
00:12:41,481 --> 00:12:44,761
"I wantcha to... say it again!"

184
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,720
You only talk in dialect
when you're in trouble!

185
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:50,370
"Well, you've been whinin' and quibblin'
for a while now."

186
00:12:50,370 --> 00:12:52,400
"Gimme a goddurn break!"

187
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:56,400
"Ya got somethin' to say, say it clearly!"

188
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,660
At least...

189
00:12:59,577 --> 00:13:04,227
At least, send me a message every day.
Are you really that busy that you can't do as much?

190
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:24,050
Was that Yoshio?

191
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:27,520
That idiot!

192
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:36,230
Excuse me, another bottle please.

193
00:13:36,230 --> 00:13:37,200
Yep, coming.

194
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:40,930
What? You had a fight?

195
00:13:41,790 --> 00:13:49,170
Yocchan is a very kind man,
but inside, he's also insecure.

196
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:55,850
You never had a
discerning eye for men.

197
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:01,250
What're you sayin.

198
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:07,790
During those days,
you're counted among those men, are you not?

199
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:17,800
Master, one more bottle.

200
00:14:18,355 --> 00:14:20,445
I only serve up to 3 bottles.

201
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,370
- Welcome.
- Good evening.

202
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:34,650
Ah! Mariko-san.

203
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:40,360
[Introduction to Go for
40 years old and above]

204
00:14:43,854 --> 00:14:47,484
Master! Give her a drink. My treat.

205
00:14:48,820 --> 00:14:49,960
Uh, look here...

206
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:52,560
You've really been studying, huh.

207
00:14:52,560 --> 00:14:54,310
It's great, right? Look...

208
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,710
You've learned this far, huh?

209
00:14:56,710 --> 00:14:58,720
I'm okaaa~y!

210
00:14:58,720 --> 00:14:59,700
Okay, okay...

211
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:03,470
Hang on a bit.

212
00:15:08,310 --> 00:15:13,110
But I didn't expect you'd get married to Yoshio.

213
00:15:15,940 --> 00:15:26,870
I thought that I made a smart choice this time.

214
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:44,950
It's possible that we may make some stupid
choices again now like we did in the past.

215
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:58,090
Koucchan...

216
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:02,620
I...

217
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:10,050
...don't do that kind of thing anymore.

218
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:15,390
It's just a joke.

219
00:16:21,330 --> 00:16:25,240
Are you really serious,
bringing me to this place.

220
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:29,730
What are you saying at this late stage.

221
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,870
You don't even know my name.

222
00:16:33,769 --> 00:16:35,149
It's Mariko-san, isn't it?

223
00:16:36,350 --> 00:16:40,210
Is there any proof that
that is my real name?

224
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:49,690
When... when men and women do it, they don't
have to know each other's names, do they?

225
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:54,190
I hate strategizing...

226
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:58,490
What are you gonna do...

227
00:17:04,339 --> 00:17:06,919
You have 1 minute to consider...

228
00:17:08,845 --> 00:17:10,545
10 seconds...

229
00:17:12,966 --> 00:17:15,036
20 seconds...

230
00:17:15,741 --> 00:17:18,251
25 seconds...

231
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:30,900
Here's your change.

232
00:17:33,310 --> 00:17:36,530
Hello. I'm sorry you had to see
us in a weird moment the other day...

233
00:17:37,881 --> 00:17:40,431
Right now, we're going
to see her parents.

234
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,270
I see.

235
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:47,780
I finally realized it...
that she's the woman for me.

236
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,080
Well, good luck.

237
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:52,720
Yes. Thanks and see you then.

238
00:17:52,856 --> 00:17:53,986
Thanks.

239
00:18:07,909 --> 00:18:09,739
He's great.

240
00:18:11,926 --> 00:18:14,926
While I'm... such an idiot.

241
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:21,150
Gimme liquor.

242
00:18:21,850 --> 00:18:25,450
Sorry... I'm closing up now.

243
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:32,460
I'm ashamed to face Mizue.

244
00:18:33,460 --> 00:18:34,630
What happened?

245
00:18:34,970 --> 00:18:37,190
Master...

246
00:18:37,190 --> 00:18:40,890
I... m-m--...

247
00:18:40,890 --> 00:18:42,780
...made a mistake.

248
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:48,210
So what are you gonna do
when you see Mizue-san?

249
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:54,680
Hiraga-san, with freshwater clams too...

250
00:18:54,680 --> 00:19:01,920
If you don't properly get rid of the sand,
you won't be able to make delicious soup.

251
00:19:25,140 --> 00:19:28,600
Welcome. It's already done.

252
00:19:34,460 --> 00:19:40,530
I must apologize to you.

253
00:19:41,780 --> 00:19:45,480
The night we fought on the phone...

254
00:19:46,850 --> 00:19:49,070
That night, right?...

255
00:19:55,380 --> 00:19:58,040
I'm the one who has to apologize to you.

256
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:01,590
What! As I thought, you and he...?

257
00:20:02,310 --> 00:20:04,780
Of course not!

258
00:20:07,980 --> 00:20:09,990
That night...

259
00:20:11,630 --> 00:20:13,660
I did some reflecting...

260
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:18,860
I needlessly gave you the wrong idea...

261
00:20:19,530 --> 00:20:23,860
It was wrong of me to
make you jealous.

262
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:32,780
I should have given you a
bit more consideration.

263
00:20:35,940 --> 00:20:39,820
Can you give me a chance?

264
00:20:45,780 --> 00:20:48,510
It may take some time but...

265
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:54,930
I want to prove my feelings.

266
00:20:59,150 --> 00:21:02,080
I'm gonna do my best so...

267
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:05,690
...please stay by my side.

268
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:24,900
Let's eat before it gets cold.

269
00:21:38,320 --> 00:21:39,910
Master...

270
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:42,750
It's delicious.

271
00:21:46,269 --> 00:21:48,189
There's more for seconds.

272
00:22:07,150 --> 00:22:11,320
When removing sand from the clams,
add a bit of salt to fresh water.

273
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:14,280
Let the clams open completely and darken...

274
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:18,680
Then simmer over medium heat,
and add the miso when it's done.

275
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:22,850
"Remaining cooking time is 10 seconds."

276
00:22:23,582 --> 00:22:26,982
"3... 2... 1..."

277
00:22:27,102 --> 00:22:28,622
"Boo~m!"

